    "content": "* President: Use of AI\n* No using AI for merch / promotion.\n* Daniel: All points to we don’t have enough attention to the procurement process. Following all standards and best pricing. We could bring it back to the table, maybe a better version of it, a better process of procurement which goes through some sort of governing body upon purchase. Now because officers can spend money with little verification, there’s little liability, you can make a mistake very easily.\n* President: Office clean pre-101 week + team bonding\n* Less of a discussion now, however we’ll do a small team bonding this summer likely around end of august.\n* President / VPFA: Budgets\n* GET DONE BY JULY 20th\n* VP Phil: Fall philanthropy campaign\n* Cat rescue, can we have cats on campus, is it viable? Need to clear with the shelter and permission from the school. Maybe a waiver for allergies?\n* Aiden: I know we had therapy dogs in the past, so I think animals are feasible, but I’m not sure if that was just because they were therapy.\n* Dakota: How would we raise money?\n* Zoe: I was thinking about a cat cafe where you can come and pay to see with maybe snacks. Also thought maybe a cat live stream? And then donate that way.\n* Daniel: I know when we do it with Hack the hill, we did it through CnR, but maybe since we’re close to the faculty maybe that’s who to contact.\n* VP Phil: (this can also be discussed w/ 101 week committee instead lol) Two rounds of shine fundraising\n* VP Franco: Moving forward with report, keeping relations with faculty intact\n* Daniel: I’d recommend checking the last meeting minutes\n* uOEC: Independence\n* Daniel:",
